quran[24]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,31,"They said: "
  68,32,"We hope that our Lord will give us in exchange a better (garden) than this. Truly, we turn to our Lord (wishing for good that He may forgive our sins and reward us in the Hereafter)."
  68,33,"Such is the punishment (in this life), but truly, the punishment of the Hereafter is greater if they but knew."
  69,28,""
  69,29,""
  69,30,"(It will be said): "
  70,22,"Except those who are devoted to Salât (prayers).{1}",1:[{70:22} See the footnote of {9:91}.]
  70,23,"Those who remain constant in their Salât (prayers);"
  70,24,"And those in whose wealth there is a recognised right"
  71,19,"And Allâh has made for you the earth a wide expanse."
  71,20,"That you may go about therein in broad roads."
  71,21,"Nûh (Noah) said: "
  72,16,"If they (non-Muslims) had believed in Allâh, and went on the Right Way (i.e. Islâm) We would surely have bestowed on them water (rain) in abundance."
  72,17,"That We might try them thereby. And whosoever turns away from the Reminder of his Lord (i.e. this Qur’ân, - and practise not its laws and orders), He will cause him to enter in a severe torment (i.e. Hell)."
  72,18,"And the mosques are for Allâh (Alone): so invoke not anyone along with Allâh.{1}",1:[{72:18} See the footnote of {2:165}.]
  73,10,"And be patient (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) with what they say, and keep away from them in a good way."
  73,11,"And leave Me Alone to deal with the beliers (those who deny My Verses), those who are in possession of good things of life. And give them respite for a little while."
  73,12,"Verily, with Us are fetters (to bind them), and a raging Fire."
  74,7,"And be patient for the sake of your Lord (i.e. perform your duty to Allâh)!"
  74,8,"Then, when the Trumpet is sounded (i.e. the second blowing of the horn)."
  74,9,"Truly, that Day will be a Hard Day -"
  75,4,"Yes, We are Able to put together in perfect order the tips of his fingers.{1}",1:[{75:4} Each human being has his or her own special finger prints not resembling anyone else, indicating that our Lord (Allâh) is the Most Superior Creator of everything: Lâ ilâha illâ Huwa (none has the right to be worshipped but He).]
  75,5,"Nay! Man (denies Resurrection and Reckoning. So he) desires to continue committing sins."
  75,6,"He asks: "